---
# Frontmatter controls how Cursor attaches this rule (Agent Chat only).
# description: Shown to the model for "Apply intelligently" style rules.
description: Sample rule for markdown and agent-instruction files in this repo.
# globs: When non-empty, can scope the rule to matching paths (see Cursor Rules docs).
globs:
  - "README.md"
  - "AGENTS.md"
  - ".cursor/**"
# alwaysApply: If true, prepended every session; if false, Cursor uses description/globs/manual @mention.
alwaysApply: false
---

# Sample project rule

When editing project docs or `.cursor` samples:

- Keep examples **valid** (JSON must parse; shell hooks must be executable if enabled).
- Prefer linking to [Cursor docs](https://cursor.com/docs) instead of duplicating full hook schemas here.
